reviewText: Here is Mariah Carey was concert that aired on NBC Thanksgiving night in 1993 in support of her Music Box album. Mariah looks absolutely stunning and at her best vocally and artistically. Too bad Mariah has a breathy voice now, she could really belt back then. I love everything about this DVD, standout performances include: Hero, Without You, Anytime You Need a Friend, Emotions, Vision of Love, and Make it Happen. This is the Mariah I liked, great voice and not trying to hard.

reviewText: I'm grateful for the re-release of this concert because I can only remember half paying attention to it when it aired on network television.  By now everyone has formed their own opinion about Mariah - but this show portrayed her as a sugary sweet Cinderella type with an undeniably powerful voice!I enjoyed some of the behind the scenes chats with her mom, the band & back-up singers but really bought this disc for the fantastic concert footage.  It was so good to see early Mariah in concert and to see her truly enjoying herself in the behind the scenes footage - she seemed a little more open and less guarded than she appears in interviews today.My favorite performances are: HERO, VISION OF LOVE & WITHOUT YOU.  I'd highly recommend this disc to fans who didn't tape this show and to those who may be curious to see Mariah at the beginning of her career.
Title: N/A

reviewText: Thank you sony for releasing this the same day as the unplugged dvd.  This was her nbc 1993 Thanksgiving special concert.  It included snippets of Mariah hanging out with friends and her mom in between performances.  This dvd includes her televised live perfomances of her early hits.  The showstopping "Anytime You Need A Friend" is my personal favorite.  Yeah they portrayed Mariah as a girl next door type with a goody goody image to bring in more fans but overall her voice is the reason this concert is worth buying.  She still is a good girl but in sexy clothing.  Enjoy it Chops.....
